"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>⦄, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(∀ <span class=\"fn\">s</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">a</span> ∉ <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Image.html#Finset.image\">image</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Insert.insert\">insert</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span>)</span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">subfamily</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>) ⦃<span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>⦄, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">({<span class=\"fn\">s</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span> | <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">a</span> ∉ <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>})</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">({<span class=\"fn\">s</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span> | <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span>})</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Induction principle for finset families. To prove a statement for every finset family,\nit suffices to prove it for\n* the empty finset family.\n* the finset family which only contains the empty finset.\n* `{s ∪ {a} | s ∈ 𝒜}` assuming the property for `𝒜` a family of finsets not containing `a`.\n* `ℬ ∪ 𝒞` assuming the property for `ℬ` and `𝒞`, where `a` is an element of the ground type and\n  `ℬ` is a family of finsets not containing `a` and `𝒞` a family of finsets containing `a`.\n  Note that instead of giving `ℬ` and `𝒞`, the `subfamily` case gives you `𝒜 = ℬ ∪ 𝒞`, so that\n  `ℬ = {s ∈ 𝒜 | a ∉ s}` and `𝒞 = {s ∈ 𝒜 | a ∈ s}`.\n\nThis is a way of formalising induction on `n` where `𝒜` is a finset family on `n` elements.\n\nSee also `Finset.memberFamily_induction_on.` ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.html#Finset.family_induction_on","kind":"theorem","line":183,"name":"Finset.family_induction_on","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.lean#L183-L205"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.html#Finset.memberFamily_induction_on\"><span class=\"name\">Finset</span>.<span class=\"name\">memberFamily_induction_on</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#DecidableEq\">DecidableEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">empty</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#EmptyCollection.emptyCollection\">∅</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">singleton_empty</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">{</a><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#EmptyCollection.emptyCollection\">∅</a><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">}</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">subfamily</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>) ⦃<span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>⦄, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.html#Finset.nonMemberSubfamily\">nonMemberSubfamily</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span>)</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.html#Finset.memberSubfamily\">memberSubfamily</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span>)</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Induction principle for finset families. To prove a statement for every finset family,\nit suffices to prove it for\n* the empty finset family.\n* the finset family which only contains the empty finset.\n* `ℬ ∪ {s ∪ {a} | s ∈ 𝒞}` assuming the property for `ℬ` and `𝒞`, where `a` is an element of the\n  ground type and `𝒜` and `ℬ` are families of finsets not containing `a`.\n  Note that instead of giving `ℬ` and `𝒞`, the `subfamily` case gives you\n  `𝒜 = ℬ ∪ {s ∪ {a} | s ∈ 𝒞}`, so that `ℬ = 𝒜.nonMemberSubfamily` and `𝒞 = 𝒜.memberSubfamily`.\n\nThis is a way of formalising induction on `n` where `𝒜` is a finset family on `n` elements.\n\nSee also `Finset.family_induction_on.` ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.html#Finset.memberFamily_induction_on","kind":"theorem","line":151,"name":"Finset.memberFamily_induction_on","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.lean#L151-L181"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.html#Finset.image_insert_memberSubfamily\"><span class=\"name\">Finset</span>.<span class=\"name\">image_insert_memberSubfamily</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#DecidableEq\">DecidableEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Image.html#Finset.image\">image</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Insert.insert\">insert</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.html#Finset.memberSubfamily\">memberSubfamily</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">s</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">𝒜</span> | <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span>}</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.html#Finset.image_insert_memberSubfamily","kind":"theorem","line":142,"name":"Finset.image_insert_memberSubfamily","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.lean#L142-L149"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SetFamily/Compression/Down.html#Finset.memberSubfamily_image_erase\"><span class=\"name\">Finset</span>.<span class=\"name\">memberSubfamily_image_erase</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_ar